history.content:
You should be teaching students for 3 hours each week.  So, if you're in CSM and teach one weekly section, you'll need to be teaching 2hrs/wk outside of that, which I think amounts to 24hrs total.

Likewise, if you have two weekly sections, you have 1hr/wk outside of that, totaling to 12hrs.  I think this is the lowest hour requirement you can get, no matter if you teach more than 2 sections/wk.

I am a CSM Senior mentor and I am trying to understand what that means in terms of my required tutoring hours for CS370. Per the course webstie it has hours listed for CSM (8 hour tutors) and CSM (4 hour tutors). Does Senior Mentor for CSM fall into either of these categories?
history.subject: CS370 Tutoring Hours Requirement
